snippet.textDisplay:
With the phones you were trying to get wet, sometimes the water doesn't get into the important parts very quickly, so they say on for a bit even underwater. This is from someone who's dropped at least 4 phones in water and 2 have broken from it. The first got completely broken, but the second one was able to be turned on once it was dry, although made a really annoying buzzing sound. And for all of them, the screens stayed lit while it was underwater and for the one that completely broke and couldn't be turned on, it wouldn't turn on after I took it apart and took the battery out to dry.
A way to see if the battery is water damaged is to look for a little white patch on the side, which will be red if it's water damaged
